The paper deals with the detection and analysis of biomedical images, specifically gel diagrams. This involves computer vision techniques for image processing and analysis, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the identification of gene names in these images, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, falling under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques for image analysis is also mentioned, which falls under the categories of deep learning (cs.DL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
